n
-\frac{1}{2} + \sqrt{n+\frac{1}{4}} \leq a_n \leq -\frac{1}{2} + \sqrt{n+\frac{5}{4}}
n=1
-\frac{1}{2}+\sqrt{1+\frac{1}{4}} \leq 1=a_1=-\frac{1}{2}+\sqrt{1+\frac{5}{4}}
n=k
\frac{1}{2} + \sqrt{k+\frac{1}{4}} \leq a_k+1 \leq \frac{1}{2} + \sqrt{k+\frac{5}{4}}
a_{k+1}=\frac{k+1}{a_k+1}
-\frac{1}{2} + \sqrt{k+\frac{5}{4}}=\frac{(k+1)(-\frac{1}{2} + \sqrt{k+\frac{5}{4}})}{(k+\frac{5}{4})-\frac{1}{4}} =\frac{k+1}{\frac{1}{2} + \sqrt{k+\frac{5}{4}}} \leq a_{k+1} \leq \frac{k+1}{\frac{1}{2} + \sqrt{k+\frac{1}{4}}}
k+1 \leq \left(\frac{1}{2}+\sqrt{k+\frac{1}{4}}\right)\left(-\frac{1}{2}+\sqrt{k+\frac{9}{4}}\right)
x=k+\frac{5}{4} \geq \frac{9}{4}>2
x \geq 2
x^2 \geq 2x>x+1
